nz.ac.auckland.morc.resource

Class HttpErrorTestResource<T extends org.apache.camel.Processor & org.apache.camel.Predicate>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nz.ac.auckland.morc.resource.HttpResponseTestResource
      • nz.ac.auckland.morc.resource.HttpErrorTestResource<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.camel.Predicate, org.apache.camel.Processor

    public class HttpErrorTestResource<T extends org.apache.camel.Processor & org.apache.camel.Predicate>
extends HttpResponseTestResource
    A resource for returning non-200 error HTTP codes back to the client, or testing that such an response was received. The default status code is 500. Setting the status code to 0 will mean it won't be validated against (but the body and headers will, if any).
    Author:
    David MacDonald - d.macdonald@auckland.ac.nz
